SandRidge Energy Inc - New Civil Antitrust Claims Filed Against Chesapeake, SandRidge Energy - The Associated Press
Thursday, 3 Mar 2016 03:46pm EST 
SandRidge Energy Inc:A class of oil and gas royalty owners has filed a civil antitrust lawsuit against Chesapeake Energy Corporation, SandRidge Energy Corp. and former SandRidge CEO Tom Ward - AP.The 14-page lawsuit, filed by attorneys with the Dallas-based law firm Burns Charest LLP, alleges that the defendants violated federal antitrust laws by rigging bids and limiting competition for oil and gas leases in northwest Oklahoma.The lawsuit states that the class could ultimately include thousands of affected royalty owners in the geological formation known as the Anadarko Basin Region."This case is about cleaning up the oil patch," says Burns Charest founder and co-managing partner Warren Burns, who represents the proposed class."In a rush to reap illegal profits, the defendants violated the trust and confidence of these royalty owners.Their actions demonstrate that they were willing to betray my clients and violate the law. We are suing to recover damages and to promote legal competition in the oil and gas industry.". 
			
Full Article





SandRidge Energy Inc 2016 job cuts total 440- NewsOk, citing the Oklahoman - Reuters
